                     Wire lines: Information about wire (also known as laid) lines
                     could contain: 

The density of the wire lines as the measure of 20 wirelines (in mm) —
                           a standard procedure common in paper descriptions;

Description of wire lines, usually in terms like: thin wire lines;
                           thick wire lines; alternating thick and thin; very thick wire lines;
                           thick wire lines, thin lines at edges; wire lines in corrugated pattern;
                           wires wrapped around the chain lines; alternate wires wrapped around the
                           chains; etc.

the process of reinforcing the spine of a sewn book after gluing-up,
                        rounding and backing, and before covering or casing-in, known as lining or
                        spine lining;

When the codex is re-bound and later end leaves and paste-downs are inserted by
                  the rebinding process this information should be entered in the corresponding
                  sections of the element binding;
